{
  "texts": [
    "SepViT blocks employ separable convolutions rather than conventional convolutions.",
    "This update minimizes the self-attention mechanism, the most computationally expensive component of ViT.",
    "Separable convolutions separate conventional convolutions into depthwise and pointwise convolutions, requiring fewer parameters and computations.",
    "RViT augments ViT design with reversible residual blocks.",
    "These blocks recreate input features from output features, which increases the efficiency of gradient calculation during backpropagation."
  ]
}